snippet.title: Superman | Official Trailer | DC
snippet.description:
Your choices, your actions, that’s what makes you who you are. #Superman - Only In Theaters and @Imax July 11

“Superman,” DC Studios’ first feature film to hit the big screen, is set to soar into theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures.  In his signature style, James Gunn takes on the original superhero in the newly imagined DC universe with a singular blend of epic action, humor and heart, delivering a Superman who’s driven by compassion and an inherent belief in the goodness of humankind. 

DC Studios heads Peter Safran and Gunn are producing the film, which Gunn directs from his own screenplay, based on characters from DC, Superman created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.

The film stars David Corenswet (“Twisters,” “Hollywood”) in the dual role of Superman/Clark Kent, Rachel Brosnahan (“The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel”) as Lois Lane and Nicholas Hoult (the “X-Men” movies, “Juror #2”) as Lex Luthor.  The film also stars Edi Gathegi (“For All Mankind”), Anthony Carrigan (“Barry,” “Gotham”), Nathan Fillion (the “Guardians of the Galaxy” films, “The Suicide Squad”), Isabela Merced (“Alien Romulus”), Skyler Gisondo (“Licorice Pizza,” “Booksmart”), Sara Sampaio (“At Midnight”), María Gabriela de Faría (“The Moodys”), Wendell Pierce (“Selma,” “Tom Clancy’s Jack Ryan”), Alan Tudyk (“Andor”), Pruitt Taylor Vince (“Bird Box”) and Neva Howell (“Greedy People”).

“Superman” is executive produced by Nikolas Korda, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars Winther.  Behind the camera, Gunn is joined by frequent collaborators, including director of photography Henry Braham, production designer Beth Mickle, costume designer Judianna Makovsky and composer John Murphy, along with composer David Fleming (“The Last of Us”) and editors William Hoy (“The Batman”) and Craig Alpert (“Deadpool 2,” “Blue Beetle”).  

DC Studios Presents a Troll Court Entertainment/The Safran Company Production, A James Gunn Film, “Superman,” which will be in theaters and IMAX® nationwide on July 11, 2025, and internationally beginning 9 July 2025, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

Go to https://groundnews.com/Ve to get all sides of every story. Subscribe to save 40% off the unlimited Vantage Plan through our link.

snippet.title: Gary Sinise Speaks Out About His Son's Death & Why He Left Hollywood | PEOPLE
snippet.description:
Gary Sinise shares his story of stepping away from Hollywood to care for his family and grieve the unimaginable loss of his son, Mac. The actor opens up for the first time about Mac’s battle with chordoma, a rare, slow-growing spinal cancer, and the strength his son showed throughout his illness: “The way he dealt with it was just pure grace and courage.” He reveals the moment they discovered Mac’s tumor on a CT scan, after months of unexplained pain: “It looks like a monster grabbing my son’s spine.” Gary reflects on a harrowing period that began with his father’s stroke, followed by his wife’s stage 3 breast cancer treatment and his son’s shocking diagnosis — and the decision he made to pause acting to care for them. Mac passed away on January 5, 2024. Gary’s wife is now cancer-free.

He has continued his work with the Gary Sinise Foundation, which supports veterans, first responders, and their families. Gary recently produced ‘Brothers After War’, a documentary about wounded heroes returning from combat, and is helping release Mac’s final music. The songs are now available, with proceeds going to the Foundation in honor of Mac’s wishes. Gary also shares the joy he finds in being a grandfather, a role that brings light amid the pain. He will return to Washington, D.C. to host the Foundation’s annual Memorial Day concert. Gary Sinise offers an intimate look at life, loss, and legacy in the wake of profound personal tragedy.

Read more: https://people.com/gary-sinise-leaving-hollywood-losing-son-to-cancer-exclusive-11733744

snippet.title: Barn Find Ford GT40: GREATEST Ever? All original & Hidden 43 Years | Barn Find Hunter
snippet.description:
The granddaddy of all barn finds! A 1966 Ford GT40 that had been stashed in a barn since 1982 now sees the light of day. In total, only 100 GT40s were made—about 30 were built specifically for the track, while the rest were made for the road. Many of the road cars were later converted into track cars, so finding an all-original road car with all its original parts is extremely rare! Follow along as Tom and the new owner, Chad, walk around and inspect this legendary time capsule.

Chicken Jockey!! Watch the movie clip from A Minecraft Movie where Garrett (Jason Momoa) must fight a baby zombie mounted on a chicken in order to save Steve (Jack Black). Welcome to the world of Minecraft, look for the movie on digital.

Four misfits—Garrett “The Garbage Man” Garrison (Momoa), Henry (Hansen), Natalie (Myers) and Dawn (Brooks)—find themselves struggling with ordinary problems when they are suddenly pulled through a mysterious portal into the Overworld: a bizarre, cubic wonderland that thrives on imagination. To get back home, they’ll have to master this world (and protect it from evil things like Piglins and Zombies, too) while embarking on a magical quest with an unexpected, expert crafter, Steve (Black). Together, their adventure will challenge all five to be bold and to reconnect with the qualities that make each of them uniquely creative…the very skills they need to thrive back in the real world.

snippet.title: Brooklyn Gets Surgery * FOR REAL * This Time
snippet.description:
I bet you’re wondering “Brooklyn gets surgery *FOR REAL* ?”....Last year I was diagnosed with a skenes gland cyst and was scheduled for surgery right after I came home from Everest. Unfortunately, when they went to remove the cyst, it had ruptured and they were unable to remove it. Well a year later,  my cyst came back in my third trimester, so it was time to go in for another surgery to have it removed, for real this time!! 

For anyone going through something like this, my heart goes out to you. The medical world is a big and confusing place and I hope nothing but the best for you!!

snippet.title: SUPERMAN TRAILER REACTION!! Official Trailer Breakdown | DC Studios | James Gunn
snippet.description:
FRIGGIN' BEAUTIFUL!! Visit https://huel.com/rejects to get 15% off your order
Superman Official Trailer Reaction, Breakdown, Easter Eggs, & Review!! James Gunn (Guardians of the Galaxy, The Suicide Squad, Peacemaker) directs Superman starring David Corenswet (Pearl, The Politician) as Clark Kent/Superman and Rachel Brosnahan (The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel) as Lois Lane.  The latest trailer also gives us a closer look at Nicholas Hoult (Mad Max: Fury Road, X-Men: First Class) as Lex Luthor, Isabela Merced (Dora and the Lost City of Gold) as Hawkgirl, Edi Gathegi (X-Men: First Class) as Mister Terrific, Nathan Fillion (Castle, Firefly) as Green Lantern Guy Gardner, and Anthony Carrigan (Barry) as Metamorpho while also demonstrating some of the film’s themes - questioning the ideals and motivations of both Clark Kent & Superman… we also get Kaiju battles, The Engineer (María Gabriela De Faría) from The Authority, Frank Grillo (Creature Commandos) as Rick Flag Sr. and MORE!
Upcoming DCU projects include The Authority, The Brave and the Bold, Supergirl: Woman of Tomorrow, and Swamp Thing, promising a diverse and interconnected cinematic universe. We also get expanded looks at Hawkgirl, Guy Gardner Green Lantern, & Mr Terrific!
